***** Course Highlights *****
This course features a set of lecture_notes transcribed by a student, and
photos from a play-testing lab session.
***** Course Description *****
An historical examination and analysis of the evolution and development of
games and game mechanics. Topics include a large breadth of genres and types of
games, including sports, game shows, games of chance, schoolyard games, board
games, roleplaying games, and digital games. Students submit essays documenting
research and analysis of a variety of traditional and eclectic games. Project
teams required to design, develop, and thoroughly test their original games.
